<item>
            <title>[SOLR-97] Rakefile now supports functional and unit tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-97</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This patch includes modifications to support both functional and unit tests split out into separate directories like RoR. The test server activation was converted from two independent functions into a singleton class with start() and stop() methods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The functional tests have been wrapped with a ensure clause so that the solr test server will always be shut down--even if an exception was tossed during testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By default the solr test server will not log startup messages to STDERR, however if it&apos;s desirable to see these you can:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   rake SOLR_CONSOLE=true&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
